article.headline: Florida A&M 27, Morgan State 16
article.story:
BALTIMORE (AP) -- Albert Chester ran for two touchdowns and
finished with 202 yards of total offense to help Florida A&M pull
out a 27-16 victory over Morgan State on Saturday night.

Chester had touchdown runs of 1 and 9 yards in the second half
to help the Rattlers win their second straight game. He completed
14 of 16 passes for 139 yards and ran for 63 yards on 24 carries as
Florida A&M (4-4, 3-2 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) handed the
Bears their second consecutive loss and fifth in their last six
games.

Rashard Pompey added 101 yards on 15 carries, including a
29-yard third-quarter touchdown run.

Florida A&M scored 20 straight points after James Meade gave
Morgan State (2-7, 1-5) an early 6-0 lead with two first-quarter
field goals.

Wesley Taylor kicked two field goals in the second quarter to
give the Rattlers a 6-6 halftime tie. Florida A&M broke through in
the third quarter when Dannell Sheppard blocked a punt on Morgan
State's first second-half possession, and the Rattlers recovered at
the Bears' 19.

Chester scored on his 1-yard run for a 13-6 Florida A&M lead.
Pompey's touchdown run gave the Rattlers a 20-6 edge with 1:29 left
in the period.

Morgan State cut the lead to 20-16 in the fourth quarter on
Jason Jackson's 4-yard touchdown run and Meade's 33-yard field goal
with 11:01 left.

But Chester led Florida A&M on a 12-play, 62-yard scoring drive
that he finished with a 9-yard touchdown run around the right end
with 4:26 remaining.
